dismissalText.commentary: Ross Lyons st Wilson b West 6 (14b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 42.85

commentTextItems.html: comes down the track to take out the spin and misses with the big shot

commentPostTextItems.html: Well that's it. Ireland have dominated this game from the early overs of Scotland innings and their precise spin bowling took them out of the game. It's been a poor performance from Scotland who never really got going.

The Irish are singing away in the away changing room while the Scottish door is locked and they're getting a stern talking to from the coaches. The weather has been lovely here in Aberdeen for a change but do join us tomorrow for the second ODI where
Scotland will try and put up a better fight to a decent Irish team.

The game tomorrow is due to start at 10.45 and the weather forecast is mixed with a few heavy showers due at some point. It could be a stop-start affair with Duckworth-Lewis involved. We will see you tomorrow but for now thanks for joining us here at

milestones.description: Porterfield has scored 8 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Niall O'Brien's record
Ireland's 97-run win against Scotland is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 86-run win against Kenya
Hamilton has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (34) for SCOT, going past John Blain
